C. Video Compression
Most complex multimedia compression type.
Video Compression Taxonomy
Video Compression
│
├── Intra-frame Coding
├── Inter-frame Coding
├── Hybrid Video Coding
├── Scalable Coding
├── Distributed Coding
└── Neural Video Coding

C1. Intra-frame Coding
Each frame compressed independently.
Similar to image compression.

Examples:
Motion JPEG
I-frames

C2. Inter-frame Coding
Uses temporal redundancy between frames.

Techniques:
Motion estimation
Motion compensation

C3. Hybrid Video Coding
Dominant modern approach.

Combines:
Prediction
Transform coding
Entropy coding

Examples:
x264
x265
SVT-AV1

C4. Scalable Video Coding (SVC)
Supports:
Multi-resolution
Multi-bitrate
Multi-quality

Used in:
Adaptive streaming

C5. Distributed Video Coding
Shifts complexity toward decoder.

Based on:
Slepian-Wolf theory
Wyner-Ziv coding

C6. Neural Video Compression
Deep learning replaces classical modules.

Research area:
End-to-end codecs
Learned motion estimation
Neural entropy coding

