Redundancy-Based Taxonomy
Compression can also be classified by redundancy removal.
1. Spatial Redundancy
Correlation among neighboring pixels.

Used in:
JPEG
HEVC intra prediction

2. Temporal Redundancy
Correlation between frames.
Used in:
Motion estimation

3. Spectral Redundancy
Correlation among color channels/frequencies.

4. Psycho-visual / Psychoacoustic Redundancy
Remove information humans barely perceive.

Critical in:
MP3
AAC
Video quantization

Entropy Coding Taxonomy
Entropy coding removes statistical redundancy.
Methods
| Method            | Use           |
| ----------------- | ------------- |
| Huffman           | JPEG          |
| Arithmetic Coding | H.264 CABAC   |
| Range Coding      | AV1           |
| ANS               | Modern codecs |


